# ResourceModel Best Practices

**Template**: [ResourceModel.hbs](mdc:docs/templates/create/ResourceModel.hbs)

## Purpose
Resource models are **DTOs** that define the JSON shape for API requests and responses.

## Requirements

- **Separate classes per operation**: `FeatureResource`, `CreateFeatureResource`, `UpdateFeatureResource`, `SearchFeatureRequest`
- **Public properties**: Use `{ get; set; }` for serialization
- **Validation attributes**: Use `[Required]`, `[StringLength]`, etc. for API-layer validation
- **JsonPropertyName**: Use when JSON name differs from C# property name
- **No business logic**: Pure data transfer objects

## Pattern

```csharp
namespace Platform.Api.ResourcesModels;

public class FeatureResource
{
    public Guid Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
}

public class CreateFeatureResource
{
    [Required]
    [StringLength(255)]
    public string Name { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}

public class SearchFeatureRequest
{
    public string? Name { get; set; }
    public int PageNumber { get; set; } = 1;
    public int PageSize { get; set; } = 10;
}
```

## Do NOT

- Include domain logic or validation beyond format
- Use domain models directly in API (always map)
- Expose internal fields like `IsDeleted`
